{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771059515,"nonce":"Ea4EPDAEhrYWE/l9XqQnbVDtUgc=","title":"Investigate file storage persistence and backup strategy","message":"ParentItem uses ActiveStorage with local Disk service. Files are stored in a Docker named volume (bonanza_rails_storage -\u003e /app/storage). Current risks:\n\n- docker compose down -v destroys all uploaded files\n- No backup strategy for attached files\n- No backup strategy for the database either\n- In production, a single docker compose down -v nukes the entire application state\n\nInvestigate:\n- Downsides of local Disk storage in a containerized production setup\n- Whether cloud storage (S3/GCS/Azure) makes more sense for production\n- Backup strategy for both the database (PostgreSQL) and ActiveStorage files\n- Whether bind mounts to host filesystem are preferable to named volumes for easier backup\n- Document recommendations in docs/plans/","files":null}]}